    "recap_headline": "Central Michigan University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "KENT, Ohio \u2013\nKent State scored four runs in the seventh inning on Sunday in handing Central Michigan a 6-4 loss in the finale of a three-game Mid-American Conference baseball series at the Golden Flashes' Schoonover Stadium.\nThe Chippewas dropped all three games in the series and are 7-10, 1-5 MAC.\nCMU plays at Notre Dame (11-6) in a nonleague game on Tuesday, March 17, and then entertains Toledo in its home-opening series next weekend. Kent State is 15-4, 5-1.\nThe Chippewas led, 3-2, when Kent State used a single and two walks to load the bases in the bottom of the seventh. Brody Williams delivered a two-run double to put Kent State in front, 4-3, and then Alejandro Covas hit a two-run single to make it 6-3.\nCole Prout\n,\nBryson Webb\nand\nHarrison Bowman\neach homered for the Chippewas, who finished with five hits. All three homers were solo shots.\nIt was Bowman's team-leading sixth homer of the season, the fifth for Prout, and the fourth \u2013 and third of the series \u2013 for Webb.\nKenny Keller\n, who relieved starter\nHayden Bailey\nto start the seventh inning, took the loss.\nBailey allowed two runs on five hits, walked three and struck out four over six innings.\nJared Hanson\n,\nNate Ross\nand\nLiam Stumpf\nalso pitched in relief for the Chippewas."
